    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Currently it's set to use the PR title for the commit message by default when you squash & merge.\r\n\r\nThe PR title defaults to the commit message if it's a single commit, but it defaults to the branch name if there are multiple. So the current behavior is correct if you create a PR before updating the changelog. But if you update the changelog first, then create the PR, it has the wrong default title.",
